title._content: Manly-Warringah Surf Life Saving float, Jubilee Day

description._content:
Photograph of the Manly-Warringah Surf Life Saving float in the Anniversary Day Jubillee procession, Sydney. The photo depicts a float with five surf-lifesavers sitting in a surfboat pretending to row and the boat is sitting on a simulated wave surrounded by seagulls. Text on the sides of the float reads: `Manly-Warringah' and `on the wings of pleasure'. The street is lined with people. On the reverse a handwritten inscription reads: 'Manly-Warringah" Surf Life Saving float Anniversay Day Jubillee Procession Jan. 1951'.

The ANMM undertakes research and accepts public comments that enhance the information we hold about images in our collection. 

Photographer: Henry Gawthorpe

Object no. 00018092
